-- Debenhams Says Moving Away from Discounts Would Be ’Suicide’
-- B y   S a r a h   S h a n n o n
-- 2013-03-13T13:17:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-13/debenhams-says-moving-away-from-discounts-would-be-suicide-.html
Debenhams Plc (DEB) , the U.K.’s second-
biggest department-store chain, ruled out reducing its reliance
on promotions like its Blue Cross sales.  “It would be suicide to move away from that,” Marketing
Director Richard Cristofoli said at a conference in London
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
